Under the rules of the Czech Republic, contracting entities may choose between open and non-open procedures.
In Germany, however, the statutory and budgetary primacy of the open procedure applies to EU-wide public procurement, which corresponds to the open procedure for national public procurement.
This will allow more companies to offer.
