Loose and suitability criteria
In the Czech Republic, there is no obligation to divide construction operations into Teillose or to award partial contracts.
An examination of the three major sections of the construction of a motorway ring showed that if selected parts were awarded separately, savings of up to €31.6 million would have been possible for a total cost of €620.3 million.
