Two-thirds of the funds spent on road construction projects in 2008 and 2009 (i.e. €2.5 billion of a total of €3.7 billion) were contracted by a total of five companies carrying out the contracts either alone or as a working group.
For 46 procurement procedures with a contract value of EUR 528 million, only two or even one tenderer submitted an offer.
The Sao showed that a reduction in market potential could lead to significant cost increases.
Additional benefits
