Preliminary information and communication
In the case of construction projects with construction services to be awarded throughout Europe, the public builder must inform interested businesses about the contracts already in the run-up to the tendering procedure.
Pre-information and communication form an important basis for Europe-wide competition.
Requirements of EU law and prevention of corruption
The preliminary information shall contain the essential elements of the procurement law concerning the planned construction projects.
They are necessary for those construction projects where the estimated total value of the contract reaches or exceeds the EU threshold and where the contracting authority intends to shorten the deadlines for offering open or non-opened procedures.
In notices, the contracting authority shall give details of the planned works contracts to be awarded throughout Europe in a mandatory manner.
