Opening up offers
During the opening date, the previously closed offers will be opened and their content will be read and made public.
From the opening date, the tenderers shall be bound by their tenders until the expiry of the contracting authority's deadline for awarding the contract.
Requirements of EU law and prevention of corruption
There are no separate EU rules for the opening of tenders.
However, the national anti-corruption rules provide for a comprehensive set of requirements to protect offers and competition during this highly sensitive phase of the award procedure.
The multi-eyed principle, as well as the transparency and traceability of the opening of tenders, should prevent manipulation and changes in submitted tenders.
